<br>
Also, as a general statement to the other posts on this thread:<br>
<br>
I think some people are under the mistaken belief that the US is about to undertake some sort of &quot;scorched earth&quot; policy in Afghanistan. I have a very firm belief that we will be targeting only those assets deemed critical to the Taliban and Bin Laden himself. Will there be civilian casualties as a result? Definitely. However, I guarantee you the US military's response will be infinitely more focused than, let's say, a couple of civilian airliners crashing into skyscrapers filled with people who were only trying to live their lives in peace.<br>
<br>
War sucks, and it is horrible that we are even put into a position of having to defend ourselves. However, now that we are, we should take care of the situation quickly, decisively and with the mindset of minimizing civilian casualties.<br>
